$section An Example Linking To Other Pages In The Same Web Site$$
$index cref, get started$$
$index link, get started$$
$index cross reference, get started$$

$head Purpose$$
The cross reference command 
$cref/cref/$$
is used to link to another destination in the same web site.
If the requested destination does not exist,
a warning is printed on $cref/stdout/$$.

$head Execute The Following Steps$$

$subhead cref_example_1.omh$$
Use an editor of your choice to
create the file $code cref_example_1.omh$$ 
in the 
$xref/
	start_simple/
	Execute The Following Steps.Test Directory/
	test directory/$$
with the following contents:
$code
$pre
     $$@begin $verbatim%cref_example_1.omh%5%#036begin %$$
$$
Note that you can copy and paste the commands above
to your editor window.
You may just copy the file with the same name from the 
$xref/getstarted/Getting Started Directory/getting started directory/$$.

$subhead cref_example_2.omh$$
