create the file $code  cref_example_2.omh$$ 
in the 
$xref/
	start_simple/
	Execute The Following Steps.Test Directory/
	test directory/$$
with the following contents:
$code
$pre
     $$@begin $verbatim%cref_example_2.omh%5%#036begin %$$
$$

$subhead Example In This Web Site Context$$
You can view the
result of making $code cref_example_1.omh$$
part of the OMhelp help web site 
by selecting 
$xref/cref_example_1/$$.

$subhead Execute OMhelp$$
In a command window and 
in the 
$xref/
	start_simple/
	Execute The Following Steps.Htm Directory/
	htm directory/$$
execute the following command
$codep
	omhelp ../cref_example_1.omh -noframe
$$


$subhead Example by Itself$$
Use a web browser of your choosing to view the file
$syntax%%test%/htm/cref_example_1.htm%$$.

